\par\plain {\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_Infidels"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 Internet Infidels}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~co-founder Jeffery Jay Lowder has argued that the presuppositional apologetics' version of TAG is fatally flawed for numerous reasons.}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transcendental_argument_for_the_existence_of_God#cite_note-8"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0\super [}}{\f0\fs24\b0\ul\ulc0\super\cf4 8]}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~First, Bahnsen fails to defend the\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 necessity}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~of Christianity instead of the mere\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 sufficiency}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~for the rational justification of the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laws_of_Logic"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 laws of logic}}{\f0\fs24\b0 , the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniformity_of_nature"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 laws of science}}{\f0\fs24\b0 , and the\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morality"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 laws of morality}}{\f0\fs24\b0 . In other words, such reasoning\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Affirming_the_consequent"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 affirms the consequent}}{\f0\fs24\b0 . Second, Bahnsen conflates "}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atheism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 atheism}}{\f0\fs24\b0 " with "}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Materialism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 materialism}}{\f0\fs24\b0 " and has really presented an argument against materialism, not an argument for Christianity. Third, Bahnsen believed that the laws of logic, laws of science, and laws of morality are\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abstract_objects"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 abstract objects}}{\f0\fs24\b0 , but Christianity arguably underdetermines the relationship between God and abstract objects. Some Christian philosophers, such as\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_van_Inwagen"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 Peter van Inwagen}}{\f0\fs24\b0 , affirm\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Platonism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 Platonism}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~and the compatibility of God and abstract objects. But other Christian philosophers argue that Platonism is incompatible with\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aseity"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 divine aseity}}{\f0\fs24\b0 .\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_Lane_Craig"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 William Lane Craig}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~urges Christian philosophers to consider anti-realist theories of abstract objects}
